Command-line TODO management

Author: Xiao Jia
Contact: me@xiao-jia.com
License: See LICENSE file

Dependency:
    ruby (mandatory; please install it using https://rvm.io if possible)
      gem install highline
    git  (optional if you don't need to upload TODOs to gist)

Installation:
    git clone git://github.com/stfairy/todo
    alias todo=`pwd`/todo/todo.rb

Usage:
    todo
      List all todo items
      They're stored in $HOME/.todo
    
    todo -h
    todo --help
    todo help
      Print help message
    
    todo Write a program
    todo "Write a program"
      Add todo item
    
    todo r c4
    todo rm c4
    todo remove c4
      Remove todo item c4
      There's no "finish a todo item"
    
    todo a4
      Show content of todo item a4
    
    todo b3 new todo content
    todo b3 "new todo content"
      Change todo item b3
    
    todo gist https://gist.github.com/12345.git
      Prepare for uploading to gist
      You have to log into gist.github.com to create one beforehand
      Create a private gist if you don't want to share it with others
      Gist URL is stored in $HOME/.todorc
    
    todo u
    todo up
    todo update
      Update todo items from gist
    
    todo c
    todo cm
    todo commit
      Update todo items to gist

